        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 8:37AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 837 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Forkland to Freddie Jones Field to near Fulton.
Movement was east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Bogue Chitto, Radford, Vaiden, Carlowville, Safford, Folsom, Central
Mills, Hazen, Minter, Selma, Craig Field Aiport, Selma Drag Strip,
Heiberger, Old Cahaba Park, Uniontown, Dannelly Reservoir, Orrville,
Dallas County Horse Arena, Vaiden Field Airport, and Barrett Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until noon CDT for
central, south central, southwestern and west central Alabama.</instruction>
